rs that:\n  1. Serve the root `/openapi/v3` discovery document listing all group/versions\n  2. Serve `/openapi/v3/apis/{group}/{version}` with the full spec for each group/version\n  3. Include etags for client-side caching of specs\n  4. Support both JSON and Protocol Buffer formats\n\n### Summary of Key Files and Functions\nThe complete chain flows through:\n1. CRD validation spec definition (`CustomResourceValidation`)\n2. Structural schema extraction (`NewStructural()`)\n3. OpenAPI conversion (`ToKubeOpenAPI()`)\n4. Spec building (`BuildOpenAPIV3()`)\n5. Dynamic controller updates (`Controller.buildV3Spec()`, `updateCRDSpec()`)\n6. API server endpoint setup (`PrepareRun()`, `InstallV3()`)\n7. HTTP handler serving (`OpenAPIService`, `RegisterOpenAPIV3VersionedService()`)\n\nThis architecture allows Kubernetes to dynamically publish OpenAPI v3 specifications for custom resources as they are defined via CustomResourceDefinitions, enabling clients to discover and validate custom resource schemas without restarting the API server."
